\chapter{Persistent State}
\label{tutorial-state}

Running a tutorial once is not enough.  The command also needs to know
whether the student is resuming, whether a finished tutorial should stay
finished until an explicit restart, and where the step workspace lives.

We therefore store the run history on disk in a simple JSON format.  The
format is intentionally transparent so that an embedded host or a human
debugging the tool can inspect it without special utilities.


