\section{Summarising progress}

The command-line interface does not need the full run history every time.
It mainly needs to know how far the student has come and where the active
workspace lives.  [[ProgressState]] is that compact summary.

<<classes>>=
@dataclass(frozen=True)
class ProgressState:
    """Compact progress summary for one tutorial."""

    tutorial_id: str
    total_steps: int
    completed_steps: int
    finished: bool
    run_id: str | None = None
    workspace: str | None = None
    updated_at: str | None = None
@

Let's verify that the summary can represent an untouched tutorial.

<<test functions>>=
def test_progress_state_can_represent_no_run_yet():
    progress = ProgressState(
        tutorial_id="demo",
        total_steps=3,
        completed_steps=0,
        finished=False,
    )

    assert progress.run_id is None
    assert progress.workspace is None
