\subsection{Loading stored runs}

Missing state should behave like first use, not like an error.

<<state store methods>>=
def load_runs(self, tutorial_id: str) -> list[TutorialRun]:
    """Load all recorded runs for ``tutorial_id``."""

    path = self.state_path(tutorial_id)
    if not path.exists():
        return []

    payload = json.loads(path.read_text())
    return [run_from_dict(item) for item in payload.get("runs", [])]
@

<<test functions>>=
def test_load_runs_returns_empty_list_for_missing_file(tmp_path):
    store = StateStore(tmp_path)

    assert store.load_runs("shell-basics") == []
@


\subsection{Saving runs}

The JSON format mirrors the in-memory dataclasses closely.  That keeps
the conversion layer small and makes the stored file easy to inspect.

<<state store methods>>=
def save_runs(self, tutorial_id: str, runs: list[TutorialRun]) -> None:
    """Persist the given runs for ``tutorial_id``."""

    path = self.state_path(tutorial_id)
    payload = {
        "tutorial_id": tutorial_id,
        "runs": [asdict(run) for run in runs],
    }
    path.write_text(json.dumps(payload, indent=2, sort_keys=True) + "\n")
@

<<test functions>>=
def test_save_runs_writes_json_file(tmp_path):
    store = StateStore(tmp_path)
    run = TutorialRun(
        tutorial_id="shell-basics",
        run_id="run-1",
        workspace="/tmp/work",
        started_at="2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00",
        updated_at="2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00",
    )

    store.save_runs("shell-basics", [run])

    assert '"run_id": "run-1"' in store.state_path("shell-basics").read_text()
@


\subsection{Looking up the latest run}

Resume and review both care about the most recent run first, so we make
that the default query.

<<state store methods>>=
def latest_run(self, tutorial_id: str) -> TutorialRun | None:
    """Return the most recent recorded run for ``tutorial_id``."""

    runs = self.load_runs(tutorial_id)
    if not runs:
        return None
    return runs[-1]
@

<<test functions>>=
def test_latest_run_returns_last_saved_run(tmp_path):
    store = StateStore(tmp_path)
    first = TutorialRun(
