\section{Restoring one run from JSON}

Runs contain nested transcripts, so we restore those first and then feed
the result to the run dataclass.

<<functions>>=
def run_from_dict(data: dict) -> TutorialRun:
    """Restore a run record from JSON-compatible data."""

    payload = dict(data)
    payload["transcripts"] = [
        transcript_from_dict(item)
        for item in payload.get("transcripts", [])
    ]
    return TutorialRun(**payload)
@

